.SH "NAME"
Photonic::LE::NP::EpsTensor
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 0.011
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 4
\&   use Photonic::LE::NP::EpsTensor;
\&   my $eps=Photonic::LE::NP::EpsTensor\->new(
\&                     epsilon=>$e, geometry=>$g);
\&   my $epsilonTensor=$epsTensor;
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Calculates the dielectric tensor for a given fixed
Photonic::Geometry structure as a function of the dielectric
functions of the components.
.SH "METHODS"
.IX Header "METHODS"
.IP "\(bu" 4
new(epsilon=>$e, geometry=>$g, nh=>$nh, smallH=>$smallH, 
            smallE=>$smallE, keepStates=>$k)
.Sp
Initializes the structure.
.Sp
\&\f(CW$e\fR PDL::Complex is the dielectric function as a complex scalar field
.Sp
\&\f(CW$g\fR Photonic::Geometry describing the structure
.Sp
\&\f(CW$nh\fR is the maximum number of Haydock coefficients to use.
.Sp
\&\f(CW$smallH\fR and \f(CW$smallE\fR are the criteria of convergence (default 1e\-7) for
the Haydock coefficients and the tensor calculations.
.Sp
\&\f(CW$k\fR is a flag to keep states in Haydock calculations (default 0)
.SH "ACCESORS (read only)"
.IX Header "ACCESORS (read only)"
.IP "\(bu" 4
epsilon
.Sp
A PDL::Complex \s-1PDL\s0 giving the value of the dielectric function epsilon
for each pixel of the system
.IP "\(bu" 4
keepStates
.Sp
Value of flag to keep Haydock states
.IP "\(bu" 4
nr
.Sp
Array of Photonic::LE::NP::AllH structures, one for each direction
.IP "\(bu" 4
epsL
.Sp
Array of Photonic::LE::NP::EpsL structures, one for each direction.
.IP "\(bu" 4
epsTensor
.Sp
The valuated dielectric tensor
.IP "\(bu" 4
nh
.Sp
The maximum number of Haydock coefficients to use.
.IP "\(bu" 4
converged
.Sp
Flags that the last calculation converged before using up all coefficients
.IP "\(bu" 4
smallH smallE
.Sp
Criteria of convergence for Haydock and epsilon calculations. 0 means
don't check. From Photonic::Roles::EpsParams.
.Sp
